Move over, Hawaiian pizza—there's a new pineapple-centric dinner in town. Here, we make an easy pineapple salsa with just fresh cilantro, lime juice, and onion for a delightfully sweet and savory condiment. It doesn't stop there, though—the juice is simmered with rich spices to create a tantalizingly sticky glaze for ground chicken thighs. It's all joined by fluffy rice, sautéed pepper and onion, smoky red pepper crema, and lime for brightness. One bite will have you totally BOWL-ed over.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

> Swap in chicken or beef for turkey—no need to break up into pieces!

== Pineapple Salsa ==

Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}(halved and thinly sliced); mince a few slices until you have 2 TBSP (3 TBSP for 4 servings).

Drain @pineapple{4%oz}(reserved juice) and roughly chop.

Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%oz}.

Zest and quarter @lime{1}.

Halve, core, and thinly slice @long green pepper{1}(halved, cored, and thinly sliced).

== Cilantro Lime Rice ==

In a #small pot{}, combine @white rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Sautéed Veggies ==

While rice cooks, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add sliced onion and green pepper; season with half the @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tbsp} (you'll use the rest in the next step), @salt, and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are browned and softened, ~{7-9%minutes}.

> If seasoning begins to brown too quickly, add a splash of water.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #medium bowl{} and cover to keep warm. Wipe out pan.

== Tex-Mex Chicken ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add @diced chicken thighs{10%oz}; using a #spatula{}, press into an even layer. Cook, undisturbed, until browned on bottom, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Break up meat into pieces and stir in @Tex-Mex paste{1}, remaining Southwest Spice Blend, and reserved pineapple juice. Bring to a simmer and cook until sauce has thickened and chicken is cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Taste and season with salt and pepper. Turn off heat.

== Assembly ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in lime zest, remaining cilantro, and @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between #bowls{} and top with chicken, veggies, and pineapple salsa. Drizzle with @smoky red pepper crema{2%tbsp} and serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.